text.tspan: Victims of human trafficking over 18 years old, Male vs. Female, 2018
The indicator is defined as the ratio between the total number of victims of trafficking in persons detected or living in
a country and the population resident in the country. This is shown for those aged 18 and older, by sex.
Source: UN Office on Drugs and Crime
